@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@orderId = 1001
@agentOne = agent.one
@agentTwo = agent.two

### =========================================================
### OmniERP Orders PoC - API Requests
### =========================================================
### Manual validation targets:
### - Health check
### - Catalog cache miss and hit
### - Demo order lookup
### - Safe optimistic-concurrency update
### - 409 conflict simulation
### =========================================================


### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health
Accept: application/json


### 2. Get order form catalogs - first request
### Expected:
### - metadata.source: slow-source
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/catalogs/order-form
Accept: application/json


### 3. Get order form catalogs - second request
### Expected:
### - metadata.source: cache
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/catalogs/order-form
Accept: application/json


### 4. Invalidate order form catalog cache
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/catalogs/cache/invalidate
Accept: application/json


### 5. Get demo order
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Accept: application/json


### 6. Successful order update
### Requirement:
### Use the current version returned by GET /orders/{id}.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Cliente Demo",
  "customerEmail": "cliente.demo@omnierp.local",
  "deliveryAddress": "Calle 10 # 20-30, Medellin",
  "internalComment": "Actualizacion realizada correctamente desde api.http",
  "statusId": 2,
  "shippingMethodId": 3,
  "version": 1,
  "updatedBy": "{{agentOne}}"
}


### =========================================================
### Concurrency conflict simulation
### =========================================================
### Expected flow:
### 1. Agent 1 and Agent 2 read the order with the same version.
### 2. Agent 1 saves first and the version increases.
### 3. Agent 2 tries to save using the old version.
### 4. Backend returns 409 Conflict and does not overwrite data.
### =========================================================


### 7. Agent 1 reads the order
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Accept: application/json


### 8. Agent 2 reads the same order
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Accept: application/json


### 9. Agent 1 updates delivery address
### Adjust version with the current version returned by the previous GET.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Cliente Demo",
  "customerEmail": "cliente.demo@omnierp.local",
  "deliveryAddress": "Nueva direccion guardada por Agente 1",
  "internalComment": "Comentario anterior del pedido",
  "statusId": 2,
  "shippingMethodId": 2,
  "version": 1,
  "updatedBy": "{{agentOne}}"
}


### 10. Agent 2 tries to save with stale version
### Expected:
### - HTTP 409 Conflict
### - code: ORDER_CONCURRENCY_CONFLICT
### - currentOrder with current version
### - attemptedChanges with Agent 2 attempted changes
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Cliente Demo",
  "customerEmail": "cliente.demo@omnierp.local",
  "deliveryAddress": "Direccion antigua que tenia Agente 2 en pantalla",
  "internalComment": "Comentario interno agregado por Agente 2",
  "statusId": 2,
  "shippingMethodId": 2,
  "version": 1,
  "updatedBy": "{{agentTwo}}"
}


### 11. Get final order and verify integrity
### Expected:
### Agent 1 delivery address remains.
### Agent 2 stale comment was not applied automatically.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/orders/{{orderId}}
Accept: application/json
